page.title: 14Flowers Of Dentdale.
page.content: Dentdale has many rare wild flowers, the Purple Spotted Orchid with spots on its leaves,is just one of the type of orchid found here.In springtime Primroses can be seen covering the banks of the River Dee,also lining the river's banks can be seen Toothwort, Kingcup,Globe Flower to name but a few. The Cuckoo_pint is common in hedgerows as are Lily of the Valley, Forget_me_not,Greater Bell_flower and many more.Speedwell grows almost anywhere with its beautiful light blue flowers;,a lovely pink flower is the Bird's_eye Primrose while the Cowslip is a delicate shade of yellow. Such a lovely variety of wild flowers can be found in the area that people need to be continually reminded to follow the Country Code and not to pick them leaving their beauty for future generations.
